<dl id="n03062b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03062b">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03062b"> 62(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> perch ze percolo (Ke<font color="green">[vin]</font>) </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Triestine <i>Perch&egrave; ze pericolo</i>: because there is danger. </mm> <blockquote class="sources">I slept with Gregory that night. Even when we were alone, I sitting on his bed, he smoking the cigarette I had given him, I couldn&apos;t win him from his reserve. I got in first. His voice changing a little, he jerked out: &ldquo;Are you sure <mark>there&apos;s no danger</mark>? Couldn&apos;t we mount guard? Jack and myself; &apos;twould be only a couple of hours each. He&apos;ll be glad to do so; I know him.&rdquo; <small> Daniel Corkery, <a name="DCHB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DCHB"><cite title="source">The Hounds of Banba</cite></a> (1920) 76-7</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
